Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, Osun State command has said the choice of women for a special squad for protection of public schools is due to inherent passion of women for the protection of children. This was disclosed by the Squad Commander, NSCDC women special squad in Osun command, Deputy Superintendent of Corps, Ayodele Adepoju. In a statement by the Public Relations Officer of the command, Olabisi Atanda, on Thursday, Adepoju, explained that the squad was ready to ensure that schools in the state were safe for learning. “We are ready to display a high level of professionalism because to whom much is given, much is expected. “Choice of female personnel for this assignment is borne out of the fact that the gender naturally has passion for the protection of children,” she said. Ayodele called on members of the public to collaborate with the squad by giving actionable intelligence and logistical support that would ensure safety in all public schools across the state.  All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com